# Copy to `.env` in this directory. Values are read by wdio.conf.mjs and forwarded
# to the app via window.__e2e.* — see src/app/root/E2EBootstrap.tsx.

# ---- Preferred: reuse a UI-added keyvault account ----
# Add an OpenAI key once via the running app (Integrations → My Keys),
# then point the spec at it by name. No `.env` API key required, and the
# real keyvault is exercised end-to-end. The default matches the canonical
# dev account.
E2E_OPENAI_ACCOUNT=vincetest1

# ---- Legacy / CI fallback: bring your own key ----
# When E2E_OPENAI_ACCOUNT is unset (or the named account doesn't exist),
# the spec falls back to addAccount + configure with this key.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your-openai-api-key
# Any chat-completions-compatible model works. `op-4.6-relay`
# (Anthropic-relayed, non-reasoning) and `gpt-4o-mini` are both verified
# in CI; reasoning models that wrap output in <think>...</think> also
# render correctly (the renderer extracts the thinking into a separate
# inline block).
OPENAI_MODEL=op-4.6-relay
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1   # optional custom endpoint

# ---- Test knobs ----
# REQUIRE_REPLY=1   # uncomment to assert on the streamed assistant text
